226void scroller_init(scroller *inst, int tag_begin, int tag_num, int p, int d,
227 int elem_sz, int _pgsz) {
228 inst->mytag_start = tag_begin;
229 inst->mytag_num = tag_num;
230 inst->prev_pos = inst->pos = p << 16;
231 inst->lim = d << 16;
232 inst->vel = 0;
233 inst->dragging = 0;
234 inst->prev_drag = 0;
235 inst->elem_size = elem_sz;
236 inst->pgsz = (_pgsz - 2) << 16;
237 inst->scrollDelay = SCROLL_DELAY;
238 /*printf("scroller init: %d %d %d %d (%d %d) %d %d\n\r", tag_begin, tag_num, p, d, pos, lim, elem_size, pgsz);*/
239}

241ft_bool_t scroller_isScrolling(scroller *inst) {
242 return (inst->vel != 0 || inst->scrollDelay != 0);
243}
244
245int scroller_mod(scroller *inst, int x) {
246 if (x < 0) {
247 x = 0;
248 inst->vel = 0;
249 }
250 if (x >= inst->lim || (x + inst->pgsz) >= inst->lim) {
251 if (inst->lim > inst->pgsz) {
252 x = inst->lim - inst->pgsz;
253 } else {
254 x = 0;
255 }
256 inst->vel = 0;
257 }
258 return x;
259}
260
261void scroller_move(scroller *inst) {
262 int _prev_pos = inst->pos;
263 inst->pos = scroller_mod(inst, inst->pos + inst->vel);
264
265 if (!inst->dragging && inst->vel) {
266 if ((inst->pos ^ _prev_pos) & ~0xffff) {
267 if (inst->vel > 0) {
268 inst->vel -= DRAG;
269 if (inst->vel <= 0) {
270 inst->vel = 0;
271 inst->pos = (inst->pos + 0xffff) & ~0xffff;
272 }
273 } else {
274 inst->vel += DRAG;
275 if (inst->vel >= 0) {
276 inst->vel = 0;
277 inst->pos &= ~0xffff;
278 }
279 }
280 }
281 } else if (inst->scrollDelay) {
282 inst->scrollDelay--;
283 /*if (!scrollDelay) printf("<scroll> delay done!\n");*/
284 }
285 /*if (inst->vel) {
286 printf("move: v=%d p=%d->%d %d\n\r", vel, pos, frac(elem_size), trunc(0));
287 }*/
288}
289
290int scroller_trunc(scroller *inst, int off) {
291 return scroller_mod(inst, inst->pos + (off << 16)) >> 16;
292}
293
294int scroller_frac(scroller *inst, int ys) {
295 if (inst->vel < 0 || inst->scrollDirection == 1) {
296 return (ys * (0xffffL - (inst->pos & 0xffff)) >> 16);
297 } else {
298 return -(ys * (inst->pos & 0xffff) >> 16);
299 }
300}

302void scroller_touch(scroller *inst, ft_int16_t p, ft_int16_t tag) {
303 int istouch = (p != -32768);
304
305 if (!istouch) {
306 if (inst->dragging) {
307 inst->dragging = 0;
308 if (inst->vel) {
309 inst->vel = DRAG * (inst->vel / DRAG);
310 if (inst->vel == 0)
311 inst->vel = (inst->pos & 0x8000) ? DRIFT : -DRIFT;
312 } else {
313 if (inst->scrollDirection == 2)
314 inst->pos = (inst->pos + 0xffff) & ~0xffff;
315 else
316 inst->pos = (inst->pos - 0xffff) & ~0xffff;
317 }
318 inst->scrollDelay = SCROLL_DELAY;
319 inst->scrollDirection = 0;
320 printf("<scroll> Done drag! %d %d\n\r", inst->vel, inst->scrollDelay);
321 }
322 inst->prev_drag = -32768;
323 } else if (!inst->dragging && inst->mytag_start <= tag
324 && tag < (inst->mytag_start + inst->mytag_num)) {
325 //atlease diff is 10 pixels
326 if (inst->prev_drag == -32768) {
327 inst->prev_drag = p;
328 } else if ((p - inst->prev_drag) >= inst->elem_size / 3
329 || (p - inst->prev_drag) <= -inst->elem_size / 3) {
330 inst->dragging = 1;
331 inst->prev_drag = p;
332 printf("<scroll> start drag! %d %d\n\r", inst->prev_drag, p);
333 }
334 }
335 if (inst->dragging) {
336 /*vel = -((p - prev_drag) << 16) / elem_size;*/
337 if ((p - inst->prev_drag) > 3 || (p - inst->prev_drag) < -3)
338 inst->vel = -((p - inst->prev_drag) << 16) / inst->elem_size;
339 else
340 inst->vel = 0;
341 if (inst->vel > 0)
342 inst->scrollDirection = 2;
343 else if (inst->vel < 0)
344 inst->scrollDirection = 1;
345 printf("Touch: %d %d \n\r", inst->vel, -(p - inst->prev_drag));
346 inst->prev_drag = p;
347 }
348}

544MediaType_e detectMediaType(const char* fname) {
545 char *s;
546 MediaType_e type = MEDIA_TYPE_INVALID;
547
548 if (((s = strstr(fname, ".avi")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 4) ||
549 ((s = strstr(fname, ".jpg")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 4) ||
550 ((s = strstr(fname, ".jpeg")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 5) ||
551 ((s = strstr(fname, ".png")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 4) ||
552 ((s = strstr(fname, ".bmp")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 4) ||
553 ((s = strstr(fname, ".wav")) != NULL && strlen(s) == 4))
554 {
555 switch (s[1]) {
556 case 'a':
557 type = MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO;
558 break;
559 case 'j':
560 case 'p':
561 case 'b':
562 type = MEDIA_TYPE_PIC;
563 break;
564 case 'w':
565 type = MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO;
566 break;
567 }
568 }
569 return type;
570}

572static ft_int32_t convertMediaFilename(const char* prefix, const char* fname, char *buffer, int sep)
573{
574 int len = strlen(fname);
575 char *s;
576
577 if (prefix != NULL) {
578 len += strlen(prefix);
579 }
580 if (len >= 252)
581 return -1;
582 if (prefix != NULL) {
583#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
584 sprintf(&buffer[2], "%s%s%s", prefix, sep ? "\\" : "", fname);
585#else
586 sprintf(&buffer[2], "%s%s%s", prefix, sep ? "/" : "", fname);
587#endif
588 if (sep) len++;
589 } else {
590 strcpy(&buffer[2], fname);
591 }
592 s = &buffer[2];
593 while(*s && *s != '.') s++;
594 while(*s) {
595 if ('A' <= *s && *s <='Z')
596 *s += 'a' - 'A';
597 s++;
598 }
599 buffer[1] = len + 3;
600 buffer[0] = detectMediaType(fname);
601 if (buffer[0] == (char)MEDIA_TYPE_INVALID)
602 return -1;
603 return (len+3);
604}

606#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
607void DisplayErrorBox(LPTSTR lpszFunction)
608{
609 // Retrieve the system error message for the last-error code
610
611 LPVOID lpMsgBuf;
612 LPVOID lpDisplayBuf;
613 DWORD dw = GetLastError();
614
615 FormatMessage(
616 FORMAT_MESSAGE_ALLOCATE_BUFFER |
617 FORMAT_MESSAGE_FROM_SYSTEM |
618 FORMAT_MESSAGE_IGNORE_INSERTS,
619 NULL,
620 dw,
621 MAKELANGID(LANG_NEUTRAL, SUBLANG_DEFAULT),
622 (LPTSTR)&lpMsgBuf,
623 0, NULL);
624
625 // Display the error message and clean up
626
627 lpDisplayBuf = (LPVOID)LocalAlloc(LMEM_ZEROINIT,
628 (lstrlen((LPCTSTR)lpMsgBuf) + lstrlen((LPCTSTR)lpszFunction) + 40) * sizeof(TCHAR));
629 StringCchPrintf((LPTSTR)lpDisplayBuf,
630 LocalSize(lpDisplayBuf) / sizeof(TCHAR),
631 TEXT("%s failed with error %d: %s"),
632 lpszFunction, dw, lpMsgBuf);
633 MessageBox(NULL, (LPCTSTR)lpDisplayBuf, TEXT("Error"), MB_OK);
634
635 LocalFree(lpMsgBuf);
636 LocalFree(lpDisplayBuf);
637}

661 //Re-allocate
662 char** newdata = realloc(inst->data, sizeof(char*)*(inst->size + FOLDERLIST_REALLOC_SIZE));
663 if (newdata == NULL) {
664 printf("ERROR! Realloc fail!\n");
665 return;
666 }
667 inst->data = newdata;
668#else
669 printf("Full folder list!\n");
670 return;
671#endif
672 }
673 inst->data[inst->head++] = strdup(fname);
674 if (inst->head == inst->size) inst->head = 0;
675 inst->csize++;
676}
677
678int _folderPop(folderList_t *inst, char* fname, size_t sz)
679{
680 if (inst->csize == 0) return -1;//empty case
681 char* name = inst->data[inst->tail];
682 inst->data[inst->tail] = NULL;
683 inst->tail++;
684 if (inst->tail >= inst->size) inst->tail = 0;
685 inst->csize--;
686 strncpy(fname, name, sz);
687 free(name);
688}
689
690void _folderDestroy(folderList_t *inst)
691{
692 int i = inst->tail;
693
694 while (inst->csize--) {
695 free(inst->data[i++]);
696 if (i == inst->size) i = 0;
697 }
698 free(inst->data);
699 inst->size = 0;
700}
701
702int _folderEmptry(folderList_t *inst)
703{
704 return (inst->csize == 0);
705}

1067enum MediaBrowserParseDB_e {
1068 MEDIA_PARSEDB_REFRESH,
1069 MEDIA_PARSEDB_FWD,
1070 MEDIA_PARSEDB_BWD,
1071};
1072
1073ft_int32_t MediaBrowser_ParseDb(enum MediaBrowserParseDB_e cmd)
1074{
1075 int res;
1076 int num = 0;
1077 int ret = 0;
1078 char *s;
1079 int i = 0;
1080 int read_ptr;
1081 int pgSz = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->rowNum*g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum;
1082 int maxSize;
1083#if defined(FT900_PLATFORM)
1084 FIL *dbFile = &g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbFile;
1085#else
1086 FILE *dbFile;
1087#endif
1088
1089#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
1090 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags & MEDIA_GLOBAL_FLAG_SCANNING) return -1;
1091#else
1092#endif
1093 if (
1094#if !defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) && !defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
1095 (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags & MEDIA_GLOBAL_NOSDCARD) || (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->storageType != MEDIA_STORAGE_TYPE_SDCARD) ||
1096#endif
1097 (cmd == MEDIA_PARSEDB_FWD &&
1098 (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size) >= g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile) //Last page, could not fwd
1099 || (cmd == MEDIA_PARSEDB_BWD &&
1100 (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start <= 0))
1101 )
1102 {
1103 printf("No parse!\n\r");
1104 return -1;
1105 }
1106
1107#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
1108 dbFile = fopen(MSVC_MEDIA_DB_FILENAME, "r+b");
1109 if (dbFile == NULL) {
1110 printf("Fail to open file db %s \n", MSVC_MEDIA_DB_FILENAME);
1111 return -1;
1112 }
1113#else
1114 res = f_open(dbFile, MB_DB_FILENAME, FA_READ|FA_WRITE|FA_OPEN_ALWAYS);
1115 if (res != FR_OK) {
1116 printf("Read Error!\n\r");
1117 return -1;
1118 }
1119#endif
1120 res = F_SEEK(dbFile, 0);
1121 if (res != FR_OK) {
1122 printf("Seek Error!\n\r");
1123 return -1;
1124 }
1125 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags |= MEDIA_GLOBAL_FLAG_PARSING;
1126 MediaBrowser_RenderUI();
1127 //Read the header first
1128 F_READ(dbFile, &g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData, sizeof(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData), num);
1129 if (num <= 0) {
1130 printf("Read header fail!\n\r");
1131 ret = -1;
1132 goto out_close;
1133 }
1134 //checking magic
1135 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.magic != MEDIA_DB_MAGIC ||
1136 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.version != MEDIA_DB_VERSION
1137#ifndef FT9XX_PLATFORM
1138 || g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.screenId != gui_moduleid()
1139#endif
1140 )
1141 {
1142 printf("Mismatching version.\n\r");
1143 ret = -2;
1144 goto out_close;
1145 }
1146
1147 //Check the command!
1148 switch(cmd) {
1149 case MEDIA_PARSEDB_REFRESH:
1150 //Get the last read pointer
1151 break;
1152 case MEDIA_PARSEDB_FWD:
1153 //Move next
1154 {
1155 int lastIdx = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx;
1156 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx += (MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER*2/3);
1157 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx + MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER) > g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile) {
1158 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile - MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER;
1159 }
1160 if (lastIdx >= g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx) {
1161 //Case not enough memory for all index
1162 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx = lastIdx + pgSz;
1163 }
1164 }
1165 break;
1166 case MEDIA_PARSEDB_BWD:
1167 //Move prev
1168 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx -= (MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER*2/3);
1169 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx) < 0) {
1170 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx = 0;
1171 }
1172 break;
1173 default:
1174 ret = -5;
1175 printf("Unknown command: %d!\n\r", cmd);
1176 goto out_close;
1177 }
1178 read_ptr = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.indexListPtr + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx*4;
1179 //Read the index
1180 if (F_SEEK(dbFile, read_ptr) != FR_OK ||
1181 (F_READ(dbFile, &read_ptr, 4, num) <= 0 && num<=0)) {
1182 ret = -5;
1183 printf("read/seek fail rptr=%d\n\r", read_ptr);
1184 goto out_close;
1185 }
1186 printf("read_ptr: %d\n\r", read_ptr);
1187 //Read data now
1188 if (F_SEEK(dbFile, read_ptr) != FR_OK ||
1189 (F_READ(dbFile, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer, sizeof(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer), num) <= 0 && num <= 0))
1190 {
1191 ret = -6;
1192 goto out_close;
1193 }
1194
1195 /*dump_buffer((unsigned char*)g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer, num);*/
1196
1197 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx;
1198 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size = -1;
1199 printf("lastRamIdx: %d indexListPtr: %d %d %d\n\r",
1200 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx,
1201 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.indexListPtr,
1202 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile,
1203 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start);
1204 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start + MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER) > g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile)
1205 {
1206 maxSize = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile;
1207 } else {
1208 maxSize = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start + MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER;
1209 }
1210// g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.lastRamIdx; ???
1211 //Now read data
1212 s = &g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer[0];
1213 for (i = 0;
1214 ((i + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start) < maxSize); i++) {
1215 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaIndex[i] = s - g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer;
1216 //Check for the next data
1217 //[0]: type, [1]: length
1218 ft_uint8_t slen;
1219 ft_uint8_t type = *s++;
1220 slen = *s++;
1221 if (((s - g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaNameBuffer) < num))
1222 {
1223 if (strlen(s) > (slen - 3)) {
1224 printf("ERROR!: %x %d '%s' \n\r", type, slen, s);
1225 ret = -7;
1226 goto out_close;
1227 }
1228 } else {
1229 //Not enough memory for file name!
1230 break;
1231 }
1232 //printf("[%d]: %x %d %s: %d \n\r", i + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start, type, slen, s, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaIndex[i]);
1233 s += slen - 2;
1234 }
1235 //The last one is null device
1236 printf("Parse %d media\n\r", i);
1237 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum > 1) {
1238 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size = (i/g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum + 1)*g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum;
1239 } else {
1240 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size = i;
1241 }
1242 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start < 0) {
1243 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start;
1244 }
1245 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start + pgSz) < (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start)) {
1246 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.size = pgSz;
1247 } else {
1248 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.size = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start - g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start;
1249 }
1250
1251 for (; i <= MEDIABROWSER_MAX_INDEX_BUFFER; i++) {
1252 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaIndex[i] = 0xFFFF;
1253 }
1254 printf("Ram Window: %d %d\n\r", g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size);
1255
1256 F_SEEK(dbFile, 0);
1257 //Update pointer if neeeded!
1258 if (cmd != MEDIA_PARSEDB_REFRESH) {
1259 F_WRITE(dbFile, &g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData, sizeof(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData), num);
1260 }
1261out_close:
1262 F_CLOSE(dbFile);
1263 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags &= ~MEDIA_GLOBAL_FLAG_PARSING;
1264 printf("Finish parsing\n\r");
1265
1266 return ret;
1267#define uart_puts(a,b)
1268}

1270ft_int32_t MediaBrowser_Scan(void)
1271{
1272 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags &= ~MEDIA_GLOBAL_UPDATED_INFO;
1273 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags & MEDIA_GLOBAL_NOSDCARD) ||
1274 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->storageType == MEDIA_STORAGE_TYPE_EFLASH) {
1275 int pgSz = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->rowNum*g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum;

1280#ifndef FT900_DISABLE_EFLASH_STORAGE
1281 //Scanning eflash

1284 END_PROFILE(eFlashScan)
1285#endif //FT900_DISABLE_EFLASH_STORAGE
1286 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start = 0;
1287 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile;
1288 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start = 0;
1289 if ((g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start + pgSz) < (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start)) {
1290 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.size = pgSz;
1291 } else {
1292 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.size = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.size + g_MultimediExp_Ctx->ramWindow.start - g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start;
1293 }
1294 } else {
1295 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags |= MEDIA_GLOBAL_FLAG_SCANNING;
1296 MediaBrowser_RenderUI();
1297 MediaBrowser_ResetMediaItem();
1298 //TODO: we can scan through the file to get list of media files and check if we need to refresh!
1299 //if (MediaBrowser_ParseDb(MEDIA_PARSEDB_REFRESH) != 0)
1300 {
1301 BEGIN_PROFILE(SdCardScan)
1302#if defined(FT900_PLATFORM)
1303 MediaBrowser_FolderScan("/");
1304#elif defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
1305 MediaBrowser_FolderScan(MSVC_MEDIA_ROOT_DIR);
1306#endif
1307 END_PROFILE(SdCardScan)
1308 }
1309
1310 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags &= ~MEDIA_GLOBAL_FLAG_SCANNING;
1311 BEGIN_PROFILE(ParseDB)
1312 MediaBrowser_ParseDb(MEDIA_PARSEDB_REFRESH);
1313 END_PROFILE(ParseDB)
1314 }
1315#ifdef ENABLE_PROFILING
1316 printf("<Profiling> Parse %d media\n\r", g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile);
1317#endif //ENABLE_PROFILING
1318
1319 //Update scroller
1320 scroller_init(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scrollobj, MEDIABROWSER_ITEM_TAG_BEGIN, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.size,
1321 //g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start/g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum,
1322 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow.start,
1323 //(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile+1)/g_MultimediExp_Ctx->colNum,
1324 (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dbData.totMediaFile+1),
1325 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->tileH,
1326 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->rowNum);
1327 printf("Done scanning!\n");
1328 return 0;
1329}

1393void helperRenderAlignedString(Ft_Gpu_Hal_Context_t * pHalContext, const char* str, enum MediaFont_e font, struct RenderArea_t *pArea, enum Alignment_e align)
1394{
1395 int len = strlen(str);
1396 ft_int8_t longfile = 0;
1397 if (font >= MEDIA_FONT_MAX)
1398 font = MEDIA_FONT_MEDIUM;
1399 struct font_info_t *pFont = &FONT_LIST[font];
1400 int xdist;
1401 if (len*pFont->w > pArea->w) {
1402 int newlen = pArea->w/pFont->w - 4;
1403 str += (len - newlen);
1404 len = newlen + 3;
1405 longfile = 1;
1406 }
1407 switch(align) {
1408 case ALIGN_LEFT:
1409 default:
1410 xdist = pArea->x;
1411 break;
1412 case ALIGN_RIGHT:
1413 xdist = pArea->x+pArea->w - pFont->w*len;
1414 break;
1415 case ALIGN_CENTER:
1416 case ALIGN_VIDEO:
1417 //xdist = pArea->x + (pArea->w - len*pFont->w)/2;
1418 //FIXME: need to count x here!
1419 xdist = (FT_DispWidth - len*(pFont->w-1))/2;
1420 break;
1421 }
1422 if (align == ALIGN_VIDEO) {
1423 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, BLEND_FUNC(ONE, ZERO));
1424 //file name
1425 helperRenderRect(pHalContext, xdist, pArea->y, xdist + len*pFont->w, pArea->y + 4*pFont->h/3, BLACK_COLOR(), 0);
1426 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, BLEND_FUNC(SRC_ALPHA, ONE_MINUS_SRC_ALPHA));
1427 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, WHITE_COLOR());
1428 } else {
1429 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, COLOR_RGB(pArea->fgColor>>16, pArea->fgColor>>8, pArea->fgColor));
1430 }
1431 //TODO: should support animation!
1432 if (longfile) {
1433 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_Text(pHalContext, xdist, pArea->y, pFont->id, 0, "...");
1434 xdist += pFont->w<<1;
1435 }
1436 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_Text(pHalContext, xdist, pArea->y, pFont->id, 0, str);
1437
1438}
1439//FIXME: Should we return the x,y after render ???
1440ft_int32_t renderStringSafe(Ft_Gpu_Hal_Context_t * pHalContext, const char* str, enum MediaFont_e font, struct RenderArea_t *pArea)
1441{
1442 struct font_info_t *pFont;
1443 const char* s;
1444 int len;
1445 int xdisp, ydisp;
1446 char buffer[128];
1447 int sz;
1448
1449 if (font >= MEDIA_FONT_MAX)
1450 return -1;
1451 pFont = &FONT_LIST[font];
1452 len = strlen(str);
1453 xdisp = pArea->x;
1454 ydisp = pArea->y;
1455 s = str;
1456 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, COLOR_RGB(pArea->fgColor>>16, pArea->fgColor>>8, pArea->fgColor));
1457 while ((s - str) < len &&
1458 (ydisp + pFont->h) < (pArea->y + pArea->h))
1459 {
1460 //FIXME: must be in buffer size limit
1461 sz = pArea->w/pFont->w+1;
1462 strncpy(buffer, s, sz);
1463 buffer[sz] = 0;
1464 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_Text(pHalContext, xdisp, ydisp, pFont->id, 0, buffer);
1465 s += sz;
1466 ydisp += pFont->h;
1467 }
1468 return 0;
1469}

1493ft_int32_t extractRiffInfo(struct MediaItem_t *pItem, struct MediaInfo_t *pMedInfo, GuiManager *CleO, int fhandle)
1494{
1495 int res;
1496 ft_int16_t num = 0;
1497 ft_uint32_t offset;
1498
1499 pMedInfo->flag |= MEDIA_INFO_INVAL_FILE;
1500#define SAFE_READ() do{\
1501 res = CMD_FREAD(CleO, fhandle, (ft_uint8_t*)g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer, sizeof(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer), num);\
1502 if (num <= 0) {\
1503 uart_puts(UART0, "Read error\n\r");\
1504 goto out_close;\
1505 }\
1506}while(0)
1507
1508 do {
1509 int i;
1510 //Try to read as much as possible
1511 SAFE_READ();
1512 for (i = 0; i < num; i+=4) {
1513 if (*(ft_uint32_t*)(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[i]) == FT_AVI_4CC_avih) {
1514 AVIMAINHEADER *pAviHdr;
1515 uart_puts(UART0, "Found avih\n\r");
1516#define uart_puts(a,b)
1517 if ((num - i) < sizeof(*pAviHdr)) {
1518 //Need to read data
1519 CMD_FTELL(CleO, fhandle, offset);
1520 CleO->cmd_FSeek(fhandle, offset - num + 1);
1521 SAFE_READ();
1522 pAviHdr = (AVIMAINHEADER*)&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[0];
1523 } else {
1524 pAviHdr = (AVIMAINHEADER*)&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[i];
1525 }
1526 pMedInfo->h = pAviHdr->dwHeight;
1527 pMedInfo->w = pAviHdr->dwWidth;
1528 pMedInfo->fps = 1000000/pAviHdr->dwMicroSecPerFrame;
1529 pMedInfo->dur = pAviHdr->dwTotalFrames*(pAviHdr->dwMicroSecPerFrame/1000)/1000;
1530 pMedInfo->flag &= ~MEDIA_INFO_INVAL_FILE;
1531 goto out_close;
1532 }
1533#if 0
1534 if (*(uint32_t*)(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[i]) == FT_AVI_4CC_WAVE) {
1535 WAVEFORMATEX_T *pWaveHdr;
1536 uart_puts(UART0, "Found WAVE\n\r");
1537 if ((num - i) < sizeof(*pWaveHdr)) {
1538 //Need to read data
1539 f_lseek(&file, f_tell(&file) - num + i);
1540 SAFE_READ();
1541 pWaveHdr = (WAVEFORMATEX_T*)&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[4];
1542 } else {
1543 pWaveHdr = (WAVEFORMATEX_T*)&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scratchBuffer[i+4];
1544 }
1545 pMedInfo->bps = pWaveHdr->wBitsPerSample;
1546 pMedInfo->freq = pWaveHdr->nSamplesPerSec;
1547 pMedInfo->flag &= ~MEDIA_INFO_INVAL_FILE;
1548 printf("bps: %d freq: %d\n\r", pMedInfo->bps, pMedInfo->freq);
1549 goto out_close;
1550 }
1551#endif
1552 }
1553 //finding the avi header
1554 }while(1);
1555out_close:
1556 return 0;
1557#undef SAFE_READ()
1558}

1560ft_int32_t extractWavInfo(struct MediaItem_t *pItem, struct MediaInfo_t *pMedInfo, GuiManager *CleO, int fhandle)
1561{
1562 struct {
1563 int f;
1564 ft_uint8_t format;
1565 ft_uint8_t bps;
1566 ft_uint8_t mode; // 1 means loop
1567 ft_uint8_t channels;
1568 int nsamples;
1569
1570 int nBlockAlign;
1571 int adpcm;
1572 int adpcmPos;
1573 int adpcmNibble;
1574 int adpcmIndex, adpcmPred;
1575 } audio;
1576 ft_uint8_t hdr[36];
1577 ft_int16_t bytesread = 0;
1578 ft_uint32_t offset;
1579 int pos;
1580 int subchunk1size;
1581 int samplerate;
1582
1583 pMedInfo->flag |= MEDIA_INFO_INVAL_FILE;
1584 CMD_FREAD(CleO, fhandle, (ft_uint8_t*)&hdr, sizeof(hdr), bytesread);
1585// dump_buffer((unsigned char*)hdr, bytesread);
1586 if (bytesread != sizeof(hdr)
1587 || memcmp(&hdr[8], "WAVE", 4)) {
1588 uart_puts(UART0, "Too small!\n\r");
1589 goto out_close;
1590 }
1591 subchunk1size = *(ft_uint32_t*) (hdr + 16);
1592 samplerate = *(ft_uint32_t*) (hdr + 24);
1593 audio.nBlockAlign = hdr[32] + (hdr[33] << 8);
1594 switch (hdr[20]) {
1595 case 0x01:
1596 pMedInfo->aufmt = LINEAR_SAMPLES;
1597 audio.adpcm = 0;
1598 break;
1599 case 0x07:
1600 pMedInfo->aufmt = ULAW_SAMPLES;
1601 audio.adpcm = 0;
1602 break;
1603 case 0x11:
1604 pMedInfo->aufmt = LINEAR_SAMPLES;
1605 audio.adpcm = 1;
1606 break;
1607 default:
1608 goto out_close;
1609 }
1610 audio.channels = hdr[22];
1611 audio.bps = hdr[34];
1612 CleO->cmd_FSeek(fhandle, sizeof(hdr) + subchunk1size - 16);
1613 //Finding chunck data
1614 struct {
1615 char id[4];
1616 ft_uint32_t size;
1617 } chunk;
1618 while ((CMD_FREAD(CleO, fhandle, (ft_uint8_t*) &chunk, sizeof(chunk), bytesread) == 0)
1619 && (bytesread == sizeof(chunk))
1620 && (memcmp(chunk.id, "data", 4) != 0))
1621 {
1622 CMD_FTELL(CleO, fhandle, offset);
1623 CleO->cmd_FSeek(fhandle, offset + chunk.size);
1624 }
1625 if (memcmp(chunk.id, "data", 4) != 0) {
1626 //goto out_close;
1627 }
1628
1629 if (!audio.adpcm)
1630 audio.nsamples = (8 * chunk.size) / (audio.channels * audio.bps);
1631 else {
1632 int sbp = 1 + 2 * (audio.nBlockAlign - 4); // samples per block
1633 int nblocks = chunk.size / audio.nBlockAlign;
1634 audio.nsamples = audio.channels * ((nblocks * sbp)
1635 + 2 * ((chunk.size % audio.nBlockAlign) - 4));
1636 }
1637 printf("bps %d nsamples %d %d\n", audio.bps, audio.nsamples, samplerate);
1638 pMedInfo->bps = audio.bps;
1639 pMedInfo->freq = samplerate;
1640 pMedInfo->dur = audio.nsamples / samplerate;
1641 pMedInfo->flag &= ~MEDIA_INFO_INVAL_FILE;
1642 pMedInfo->nsamples = audio.nsamples;
1643out_close:
1644 return 0;
1645}

1797void helperRenderProgressBar(Ft_Gpu_Hal_Context_t *pHalContext, int xdist, int ydist, int xdist2, int curTimeSecs, int endTimeSecs, ft_uint8_t tag, float ratio)
1798{
1799 char buffer[16];
1800 int x2 = 0;
1801 int progbar_start = xdist/2;
1802 int progbar_end = xdist2;
1803
1804 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, WHITE_COLOR());
1805 //Render current played time
1806 sprintf(buffer, "%02d:%02d", SECOND2MIN(curTimeSecs), SECOND2REMAIN(curTimeSecs));
1807 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_Text(pHalContext, xdist/2 - 8*3, ydist - 15 - 10, 28, 0, buffer);
1808
1809 //Render full time
1810 sprintf(buffer, "%02d:%02d", SECOND2MIN(endTimeSecs), SECOND2REMAIN(endTimeSecs));
1811 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_Text(pHalContext, xdist2 - 8*3, ydist - 15 - 10 , 28, 0, buffer);
1812
1813 //Render progress bar
1814 if (ratio > 1.0)
1815 ratio = 1.0;
1816 if (ratio < 0.0)
1817 ratio = 0.0;
1818 x2 = (int)(progbar_start + (float)(progbar_end - progbar_start)*ratio);
1819 if (x2 < progbar_start) x2 = progbar_start + 1;
1820
1821 //Draw line
1822 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, TAG(tag));
1823 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, BEGIN(LINES));
1824 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, LINE_WIDTH(3 * 16));
1825 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, VERTEX2F((progbar_start)*16, (ydist)*16));
1826 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, VERTEX2F((x2)*16, (ydist)*16));
1827 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, LINE_WIDTH(1 * 16));
1828 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, VERTEX2F((x2)*16, (ydist)*16));
1829 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext, VERTEX2F((progbar_end)*16, (ydist)*16));
1830
1831 //Invisible status bar for seeking
1832 helperRenderInvisibleLine(pHalContext, progbar_start*16, (ydist-14)*16, progbar_end*16, (ydist-10)*16, 16*16, tag);
1833
1835 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext,COLOR_A(255));
1836 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext,BEGIN(FTPOINTS));
1837 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext,POINT_SIZE(10*16));
1838 //TODO: sample value, should render correct value here!
1839 EVE_Cmd_wr32(pHalContext,VERTEX2F((x2)*16,(ydist)*16));
1840}

2789 Ft_Gpu_CoCmd_LoadIdentity(pHalContext);

2792}

2807int getMediaFileStatus(struct MediaItem_t *mediaItem, struct MediaInfo_t *info, GuiManager *CleO)
2808{
2809#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
2810 char fname[MAX_PATH];
2811 sprintf(fname, "%s%s", MSVC_MEDIA_ROOT_DIR, mediaItem->fname);
2812#else
2813 char* fname = mediaItem->fname;
2814#endif
2815 info->h = -1;
2816 info->w = -1;
2817 info->flag = 0x0;
2818 info->fps = -1;
2819 info->dur = 0;
2820
2821 int h = CleO->cmd_FOpen(fname, FILE_READ);
2822 if (h < 0) {
2823 return h;
2824 }
2825 CMD_FSIZE(CleO, h, info->fsize);
2826
2827 if (mediaItem->fname[0] == '@') {
2828 info->flag = MEDIA_INFO_EFLASH_FILE;
2829 }
2830 switch (mediaItem->type) {
2831 case MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
2832 extractRiffInfo(mediaItem, info, CleO, h);
2833 break;
2834 case MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO:
2835 extractWavInfo(mediaItem, info, CleO, h);
2836 //extractRiffInfo(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaItem[idx], &g_MultimediExp_Ctx->mediaInfo);
2837 break;
2838 case MEDIA_TYPE_PIC:
2839 extractJpegInfo(mediaItem, info, h);
2840 break;
2841 }
2842 CleO->cmd_FClose(h);
2843 return 0;
2844}

2866int helperPlayMedia(struct MediaItem_t *mediaItem, Ft_Gpu_Hal_Context_t *pHalContext, GuiManager *CleO, ft_uint8_t *mediaCmd, char* bufferCmd)
2867{
2868 int aret = -1;
2869
2870 strncpy(bufferCmd, mediaItem->fname, MEDIA_COMMAND_BUFFER_SIZE);
2871 if (mediaItem->type == MEDIA_TYPE_AUDIO) {
2872 *mediaCmd = MEDIA_TYPE_INVALID;
2873 if (strcmp(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->audioFile, mediaItem->fname)) {
2874 strncpy(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->audioFile, mediaItem->fname, MEDIA_COMMAND_BUFFER_SIZE);
2875 } else if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags & MEDIA_GLOBAL_AUDIO_PLAYING) {
2876 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags |= MEDIA_GLOBAL_AUDIO_CONT_PLAYING;
2877 }
2878 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->state = MEDIA_STATEMACHINE_PLAY_AUDIO;
2879 aret = MultimediaExplorer_AppPlayAudio(pHalContext, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->CleO, g_MultimediExp_Ctx->audioFile);
2880 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->state = MEDIA_STATEMACHINE_MAIN;
2881 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags &= ~MEDIA_GLOBAL_AUDIO_CONT_PLAYING;
2882 } else if (mediaItem->type == MEDIA_TYPE_PIC) {
2883 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->state = MEDIA_STATEMACHINE_VIEW_PICTURE;
2884 aret = MultimediaExplorer_AppViewPicture(pHalContext, CleO, bufferCmd);
2885 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->state = MEDIA_STATEMACHINE_MAIN;
2886 //Extract media info
2887 } else {
2888 *mediaCmd = MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO;
2889 aret = MEDIAPLAYER_KEY_EXIT;
2890 }
2891 return aret;
2892}

2895union progInfo_t {
2896 int8_t buf[256];
2897 struct {
2898 int8_t marker;
2899 int8_t length;
2900 int8_t percent;
2901 char name[253];
2902 };
2903};
2904
2905const char* fileProgDb = "/System/prog.db";
2906int findMediaFile(FIL *pFile, const char* filename, union progInfo_t *pInfo)
2907{
2908 UINT rnum = 0;
2909 int read_ptr = 0;
2910 FRESULT res;
2911 FILINFO fileinfo;
2912 int len = strlen(filename);
2913
2914 if(sdhost_card_detect() != SDHOST_CARD_INSERTED) {
2915 //No sdcard to saving info now!
2916 return -1;
2917 }
2918 res = f_open(pFile, fileProgDb, FA_READ|FA_WRITE|FA_OPEN_ALWAYS);
2919 if (res != FR_OK) {
2920 return -1;
2921 }
2922#if _USE_LFN
2923 fileinfo.lfname = NULL;
2924 fileinfo.lfsize = 0;
2925#endif
2926 f_lseek(pFile, 0);
2927 read_ptr = 0;
2928 while(f_read(pFile, (void*)pInfo, sizeof(*pInfo), &rnum) == FR_OK) {
2929 if (rnum == 0)
2930 return -1;
2931 if (pInfo->marker != (int8_t)0xFF) {
2932 //Invalid file
2933 f_lseek(pFile, read_ptr);
2934 f_truncate(pFile);
2935 break;
2936 }
2937 if (!strncmp(pInfo->name, filename, len)) {
2938 //Found this
2939 f_lseek(pFile, read_ptr);
2940 return read_ptr;
2941 }
2942 read_ptr += pInfo->length;
2943 pInfo->name[252] = 0;
2944 f_lseek(pFile, read_ptr);
2945 }
2946 return -1;
2947}

2949extern "C" int MultimediaExplorer_SetFileProgress(const char* filename, uint8_t percent)
2950{
2951 FRESULT res;
2952 FIL file;
2953 union progInfo_t info;
2954 UINT rnum = 0;
2955 int read_ptr = 0;
2956
2957 read_ptr = findMediaFile(&file, filename, &info);
2958 if (read_ptr < 0) {
2959 //New file:
2960 info.marker = 0xff;
2961 info.length = strlen(filename) + 3;
2962 strcpy(info.name, filename);
2963 //info.name[252] = 0;
2964 info.percent = percent;
2965 } else {
2966 info.percent = percent;
2967 }
2968 res = f_write(&file, &info, info.length, &rnum);
2969 f_close(&file);
2970 if (res != FR_OK) {
2971 printf("Fail to write!\n\r");
2972 return -1;
2973 }
2974 return 0;
2975}

2977extern "C" int8_t MultimediaExplorer_GetFileProgress(const char* filename)
2978{
2979 union progInfo_t info;
2980 FRESULT res;
2981 int read_ptr;
2982 FIL file;
2983
2984 read_ptr = findMediaFile(&file, filename, &info);
2985 if (read_ptr < 0) {
2986 return -1;
2987 }
2988 f_close(&file);
2989 return info.percent;
2990}

3235 switch(g_MultimediExp_Ctx->PrevTag) {
3236#if !defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) && !defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
3237#ifndef FT900_DISABLE_EFLASH_STORAGE
3238 case MEDIAPLAYER_KEY_EFLASH:
3239#endif
3240 case MEDIAPLAYER_KEY_SDCARD:
3241 if ((ft_uint8_t)g_MultimediExp_Ctx->storageType != g_MultimediExp_Ctx->PrevTag) {
3242 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->storageType = (enum MediaStorageType_e)g_MultimediExp_Ctx->PrevTag;
3243 MediaBrowser_Scan();
3244 }
3245 break;
3246#endif
3247 case MEDIAPLAYER_KEY_EXIT:
3248 goto media_command;
3249 }
3250 }
3251 }
3252 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->state == MEDIA_STATEMACHINE_MAIN) {
3253 scroller_move(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scrollobj);
3254 if (scroller_isScrolling(&g_MultimediExp_Ctx->scrollobj) || g_MultimediExp_Ctx->PenDown) {
3255 g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags &= ~MEDIA_GLOBAL_UPDATED_INFO;
3256 } else {
3257 updateMediaCompactInfo();
3258 }
3259 }
3260 if (g_MultimediExp_Ctx->UiFlags & MEDIA_GLOBAL_AUDIO_PLAYING) {
3261 CleO->service_playback();
3262 }
3263 }
3264 }

3267 /*Ft_Gpu_Hal_WrMem(pHalContext, RAM_DL,(ft_uint8_t *)FT_DLCODE_BOOTUP,sizeof(FT_DLCODE_BOOTUP));

3271 CleO->cmd_AudioStop();
3272 }
3273 FT_Util_ExitApp(pHalContext);
3274#if defined(FT900_PLATFORM)
3275 ft_millis_exit();
3276#endif
3277 //Backup some minimal status
3278 lastStorage = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->storageType;
3279 lastDispWindow = g_MultimediExp_Ctx->dispWindow;
3280
3281 //Restore GUI manager running context
3282 free(g_MultimediExp_Ctx);
3283 g_MultimediExp_Ctx = NULL;
3284 if (mediaCmd != MEDIA_TYPE_INVALID) {
3285 //TODO: check if the file is exist!, if not we raise error trap!
3286 switch(mediaCmd)
3287 {
3288 case MEDIA_TYPE_VIDEO:
3289 //TODO: return to app or exit!
3290#if defined(MSVC_PLATFORM) || defined(BT8XXEMU_PLATFORM)
3291 {
3292 char videoPath[MAX_PATH];
3293
3294 sprintf(videoPath, "%s\\%s", MSVC_MEDIA_ROOT_DIR, g_CmdBuffer);
3295 ret = AppAviPlayer(pHalContext, videoPath, 1, 1);
3296 CleO->end_audio();
3297 }
3298#else
3299 ret = AppAviPlayer(pHalContext, g_CmdBuffer, 1, 1);
3300 CleO->end_audio();
3301#endif //
3302#ifdef FT9XX_PLATFORM
3303 Gpu_Hal_WaitCmdfifo_empty(pHalContext);
3304#endif
3305 break;
3306 }
3307 if (ret == MEDIAPLAYER_KEY_BACK) {
3308 goto again;
3309 }
3310 }
3311/*
3312 uart_puts(UART0, "Exit MediaPlayer!\n\r");
3313*/
3314#ifndef FT9XX_PLATFORM
3315exit_app:
3316 gui_restore();
3317#endif //FT9XX_PLATFORM
3318
3319 if (ret < 0) {
3320 return ret;
3321 }
3322 return 0;
